%N A395320 Decimal expansion of the conjecturally maximum possible volume of a polyhedron with 14 vertices inscribed in the unit sphere.
%C A395320 Also least positive root of the polynomial 729*x^4 - 7776*x^3 + 36864*x + 16384.
%H A395320 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A395320/b395320.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A395320 Hugo Pfoertner, <a href="https://www.randomwalk.de/sphere/volmax/pages/14.htm">Visualization of Polyhedron</a>, (1999).
%H A395320 Hugo Pfoertner, <a href="https://www.randomwalk.de/sphere/volmax/videos/14c.mp4">Number of edges incident with the 14 vertices</a>, video (2021).
%H A395320 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_04">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 4</a>.
%F A395320 Equals (8/9)*(sqrt(2) + 1)*(3 - sqrt(3)). - _Paolo Xausa_, Apr 19 2026
%e A395320 2.7209778993486486708269651168154048682669...
